name: ΛVΛ XYZ
tweet: We expect to see fashion make a full crossover into the metaverse as more brands leverage this new digital space. Did you tune into  #MVFW ? if so sound off below and share your favorite NFT fashion below! ✍️by @LuckyGa74882673  #Metaverse #Wearables #NFT

name: ΛVΛ XYZ
tweet: However, we see the success of this first Metaverse Fashion week as a sign that fashion just may be ready to go fully digital and explore wearables.

name: ΛVΛ XYZ
tweet: While Metaverse Fashion week took off without a hitch, there were some small tech issues mainly with software which caused some accessibility issues for those attending.  https://t.co/UulBpzRaHW

name: ΛVΛ XYZ
tweet: In addition to digital wearables on 3D avatars, MVFW showcased pop-ups from retailers selling NFT digiphysical items. Like, Privé Porter, who had its luxury resale pop-up shop in Decentraland’s Threedium Plaza.  https://t.co/hNz1rzGXEu

name: ΛVΛ XYZ
tweet: Another participant in the first digital fashion week, German fashion designer Philipp Plein also participated in this year's MVFW and showcased his NFT collection in the designs house newly acquired $1.4 million Plein Plaza, which is a plot of land in the Decentraland metaverse.  https://t.co/7ROKk3plQv

name: ΛVΛ XYZ
tweet: Unlike any other fashion week, #MVFW  included brands and designers who displayed wearable nonfungible tokens (NFTs) on 3D avatars. While the idea of digital fashion is not new, fashion designers praised MVFW as one of the most exciting ways for brands to engage with consumers.  https://t.co/tkiLmwNBvD

name: ΛVΛ XYZ
tweet: #MVFW hosted artists and designers including fashion giants like Tommy Hilfiger, Estée Lauder, Philipp Plein, Selfridges and Dolce & Gabbana.  https://t.co/1TG6aop7kE
